content: There is no doubt this is a visually fantastic looking app. However, in terms of functionality, this app is utterly diresome, frankly useless. First, the location is always completely inaccurate, to the order of at least 100 miles. This is despite the app using the most aggressive location service settings. A knock-on problem of the location setting is then the vastly increased battery drain compared to similar apps (usage monitor confirms this). The real crux of the utter failure of this app is the poor accuracy of the actual weather forecast. Temperature reports from this app are frequently wrong to the order of 5 or 6 degrees C, at best it is 3 deg C wrong. This is compared with the BBC app, the official UK Met Office app, and a variety of highly regarded independent apps using either official Met Office data, Foreca data (and others). These faults and errors are replicated in total on eight other Android devices (owned either by myself, my wife, and other family relatives) in various locations. Sad, because this app promised so much, yet failed so consistently.
replyContent: Could you please specify the exact location where you observe this? What is the actual weather that you see and when did it happen? Thank you in advance for your answer.

This really is a beautiful weather app. The widget goes well with any theme. Annnnnd, that's what got it the second star in this review, design and concept.   The weather forecasts are consistent, consistently dead wrong.   While at home his morning, it said that it was overcast outside with rain throughout tomorrow. There isn't a cloud in the sky here. It also says it's 86¬∞ F by my tracked location, but 90¬∞F by my saved location, which are each the same place right now. I wouldn't bother mentioning this if it were off by 1-2¬∞, but 4¬∞ is pretty steep for a weather app.   They've added a "Report Weather" function, but I use weather apps to have the weather reported to me, not the other way around. I'm embarrassed to say that I paid for this. I would have been better off setting that money on fire to stifle the odors from my toddler's fecal matter. I even canceled a cookout a day in advance because it forecasted pouring rain. I'm sure you can imagine what didn't happen; that's right, the cookout nor the rain.   If you want a pretty app that looks like a weather app, but don't actually care about the weather, this is the app for you. If you actually want to know what's going to be happening outside, look elsewhere.

The app does a really good job of getting me the information that I want about what the weather is currently like, and probably will be like for the next few days.  It has pseudo-hourly forecast (every 3 hours) for the upcoming 24 hours or so.  It packs a lot of information onto one screen which I think is the best thing about the app.  If I could add one feature it would be to drill down into the hourly forecast and see the chance of precipitation at a given time during the day.  For the functionality and presentation I give the app 3 stars.  I would give it more, but it seems to cause blocking in my system UI.  I have narrowed it down to this app that is the culprit.  When I unlock my screen, I often can't do anything for 1-3 second, presumably while my widget updates the temperature.
